data.name: label4.ToolTip
data.value: Using this table you can add / remove / update or simply view the NPC names and related ID that is used in other tabs. It is not what's currently present in the game database, of course, just a way to input/edit this info inside the software. Only using the SQL Creator in this tab (below this table) that you can create SQL Queries for adding NPCs to the ArtaCore database. Take care of adding Names+IDs in this internal database so they match what you have imported in the ArtaCore server.

data.name: cbEnableItemNameFetching.ToolTip
data.value: Check this to fetch the item names from the IDs pasted in the Item IDs list form woltk.db.com. If an item is not found it will be shown an error message and the item itself will be marked in red. This takes time!

data.name: cbAutoGenerateStarterEnder.ToolTip
data.value: Check this if you have input an NPC of your choice in the upper right field and if you want ALL the quests in the query above to be assigned to that NPC for both the quest starter and quest ender. This will generate appropriate queries for this automatically.

data.name: cbNPCIDEQuestTemplate.ToolTip
data.value: Select the NPC creature id who will be the starter and ender for this quest. This field is taken into account only if you have selected the "Create QuestStarter/Ender as well" checkbox. Otherwise it is ignored.
